Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[,kɔri'ɔgrəfi]
*danh từ
 ■nghệ thuật bố trí điệu múa ba-lê

Anh - Anh
choreography
[ˌkɒrɪ'ɒgrəfi]
■ noun the sequence of steps and movements in dance, especially ballet.
⁃ the practice of designing steps and movements in dance.
Derivatives
choreographicadjective
choreographicallyadverb
Origin
C18 (in the sense 'written notation of dancing'): from Gk khoreia 'dancing in unison' (from khoros 'chorus') + -graphy.
